CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 23, 1953, pg. 27, reads: "More LL Officials - As the time draws near for the opening of the Uptown Little League, more and more officials are being signed for the important roles they will be called upon to play in running of the circuit. Above D.M. Jones is shown signing to manage the North Side Elks team and Jasper Campbell, business manager, looks on.  Other key workers in the league are shown watching the proceedings.  They are, left to right, John McCollum, Wally Sullivan and Thomas Harper. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: D. M. Jones signing to manage North Side Elks Little League baseball team, with Jasper Campbell seated on right, and standing from left: John McCollum, Wally Sullivan, and Thomas Harper, in Ammon Recreation Center
